HEADWORD: Dogwatch
<hw>Dog"watch`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A half watch; a watch of two hours, of which there are two, the
first <ex>dogwatch</ex> from 4 to 6 o'clock, p. m., and the second
<ex>dogwatch</ex> from 6 to 8 o'clock, p. m.</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dog-weary</ent>⟦br⟧
